data.title: Mingus Big Band On JazzSet
data.meta_description: Charles Mingus has one of the largest bodies of composition in 20th-century American music, second only to that of Duke Ellington. The mighty Mingus Big Band ramps it up, beginning with "Gunslinging Bird," and charges ahead from there at the Jazz Standard in New York City.
